Header.title: ECE Outreach
Header.paragraph: Students of Colorado State University bringing passion for Electrical and Computer Engineering to students from middle school to college.

About.paragraph: ECE Outreach is devoted to making Electrical and Computer Engineering more accessible to students by delivering it in small, exciting, and informative packages. Our team works to develop exciting workshops and inspiring demonstrations, opening up the world of electronics to students who may never have considered this exciting path for their education and career.

Team.description: I really enjoy climbing and playing hockey! These let me clear my head and relax. I also really like to design and build speakers in my free time. It isn't the cheapest hobby but I really enjoy it!

Team.name: Jacklyn Moore
Team.description: I am a senior in both Electrical Engineering & Biomedical Engineering. I am part of the Math Team in ECE Outreach, and I am interested in pursuing a career in cardiology!

Team.name: Kendra Ott
Team.description: I'm a senior in Computer Engineering and I lead the math team. I love programming and am interested in firmware.

Team.description: I‚Äôm an Electrical Engineering senior and lead for the EV3 Robotics team. I‚Äôm here because I believe outreach is one of the most important endeavors we can take on as engineering students.

Team.name: Vani Kapoor
Team.description: I am a Senior Electrical Engineering student. I have been a part of the outreach team since my sophomore year. I am interested in going into project management in the automotive industry.

Team.name: Ben Beauvais
Team.description: I am a senior in Electrical Engineering and the school contact lead for ECE Outreach.  My career interests lie in energy and telecommunications, but I also have a passion for teaching engineering and mentoring younger students!

Team.name: Gwyn Tari
Team.description: Gwyndolyn Tari is a computer engineering student with a passion for animatronics and computer hardware.

Team.name: Ethan Schultz
Team.description: I am a junior majoring in Electrical Engineering. I really enjoy programming and working on side projects.

Team.name: Naser Moin
Team.description: I am a third year undergraduate in computer engineering. My interests include software and digital systems, and I also have a passion for teaching others.

Team.name: Matt Gilmore
Team.description: My name is Matt, and I am a junior EE student who enjoys fly fishing and building PC's when I have free time.

Team.name: Thomas Balzer
Team.description: I am a sophomore electrical engineering student interested in controls and robotics.

Team.name: Ticus Brandt
Team.description: I am a sophomore in Computer Engineering. I have a passion for inventing and innovating and using any chance to get creative.

Team.name: Pacen Whited
Team.description: I am a sophomore computer engineering student and have an interest in software development and embedded systems.

Team.name: Kailee Mitsuyasu
Team.description: Hi my name is Kailee. Professionally, I am interested in VLSI, circuit design, and embedded systems. In my spare time I love to cook and play the guitar.

Alumni.name: Jameson Richard
Alumni.quote: ECE opens up a world of potential, both for your career prospects and for your free time.

Alumni.name: Joseph Stubitz
Alumni.quote: ECE majors help keep the lights on and are powering us toward the future.

Alumni.name: Jarvis Hill
Alumni.quote: Give 100% in the current moment; it will always lead to your next greatest moment; you‚Äôll never have to sit around wondering in a null state of life.

Alumni.name: Ian Bernstein
Alumni.quote: With sensors, microcontrollers, and computers surrounding us from our cars to our fitness equipment to sleep aids, ECE is becoming more and more important every day. Not to mention how fun, creative, and rewarding it can be!

Alumni.name: Cole Taylor
Alumni.quote: I am excited to start a meaningful career in the aerospace industry. I will be working for Lockheed Martin Space as a test engineer.

Alumni.name: Blake Danis
Alumni.quote: I am currently working for a fantastic company in Colorado Springs as a Development Engineer where I‚Äôm learning more about RF circuit design and getting lots of hands-on hardware excitement!
